From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Jeongseok Lee <jeongseok@meta.com>
Date: Fri, 1 Nov 2024 23:25:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Set CMake policy CMP0148 for python_add_library command

pybind11 2.13.6 requires the python_add_library() command which is
provided by CMake's FindPython3 module. This command is only available
when policy CMP0148 is set to NEW (use FindPython3 instead of deprecated
FindPythonInterp/FindPythonLibs).

Set the policy before finding pybind11 to ensure python_add_library is available.

Fixes: Unknown CMake command "python_add_library"
---
 pymomentum/CMakeLists.txt | 5 +++++
 1 file changed, 5 insertions(+)

diff --git a/pymomentum/CMakeLists.txt b/pymomentum/CMakeLists.txt
index 1111111..2222222 100644
--- a/pymomentum/CMakeLists.txt
+++ b/pymomentum/CMakeLists.txt
@@ -35,6 +35,11 @@ if(MOMENTUM_ENABLE_SIMD)
   target_compile_definitions(pymomentum_common INTERFACE MOMENTUM_ENABLE_SIMD)
 endif()

+# Set CMake policy to use modern FindPython3 module
+# This enables python_add_library() command required by pybind11 2.13.6
+if(POLICY CMP0148)
+  cmake_policy(SET CMP0148 NEW)
+endif()

 find_package(Torch REQUIRED)
 find_package(pybind11 REQUIRED)
--
2.47.0
